# Article dashboard — sentiment panel (server-rendered from Omeka item
# metadata via SentimentExtractor). Strings originate from the retired
# IwacSentiment module so existing installations' translation memory
# keeps working.
msgid "AI sentiment"
msgstr "Sentiment IA"

msgid "Polarity"
msgstr "Polarité"

msgid "Centrality"
msgstr "Centralité"

msgid "Subjectivity"
msgstr "Subjectivité"

msgid "Show reasoning"
msgstr "Voir les justifications"

msgid "Model comparison"
msgstr "Comparaison des modèles"

msgid ""
"Polarity, centrality to Islam and Muslim communities, and subjectivity "
"ratings for this article, produced by three AI models (Gemini 3 Flash, GPT-5"
" mini, Ministral 14B). Read directly from the Omeka item metadata."
msgstr ""
"Polarité, centralité à l’islam et aux communautés musulmanes, et "
"subjectivité de cet article, évaluées par trois modèles d’IA (Gemini 3 "
"Flash, GPT-5 mini, Ministral 14B). Lues directement depuis les métadonnées "
"de la notice Omeka."

msgid ""
"Scales: polarity 1 (very negative) – 5 (very positive) · centrality 1 (not "
"addressed) – 5 (very central) · subjectivity 1 (objective) – 5 (subjective)"
msgstr ""
"Échelles : polarité 1 (très négatif) – 5 (très positif) · centralité 1 (non "
"abordé) – 5 (très central) · subjectivité 1 (objectif) – 5 (subjectif)"

